CRF Annotation: Mandatory Rules and Best Practices
Purpose
This note defines the mandatory rules and best practices for Clinical Report Form (CRF) annotation. The objective is to ensure complete traceability, CDISC SDTM compliance, and regulatory readiness of clinical trial data from data collection through submission.
CRF annotation serves as a key traceability document linking collected CRF data to SDTM datasets and must be prepared with a regulatory reviewer mindset.

Scope
This guidance applies to:
SDTM Programmers
Clinical Data Programmers
Programming Leads and QC teams
Studies intended for regulatory submission (FDA, EMA, PMDA, etc.)

